#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:2
#: dd9b0d1018fc43ce91e4121629b033e8
msgid "Plasticity 3D"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:4
#: 892d5644516e48a082fc200f389b8a74
#, python-format
msgid ""
"The 3D extension of :doc:`plasticity_strip`: J2 flow theory with linear "
"isotropic hardening on a :math:`0.5 \\times 0.5 \\times 0.5` m steel "
"cube, stretched 40 % in the :math:`x` direction over 50 loading steps and"
" unloaded over 50 more. The script is "
"``examples/solid/plasticity_3d/plasticity_3d.py``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:10
#: 4864ffc3802844d7a3f1b940d0483fb6
msgid ""
"The constitutive model, the variational-update pattern, and the history-"
"variable bookkeeping are **identical** to the 2D version — "
":class:`~tensormesh.assemble.J2Plasticity` is dimension-generic. What "
"changes here is scale, so the page focuses on what's actually different "
"rather than re-stating the J2 model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:18
#: 371959672c204185823e9217689ff76c
msgid "Differences from the 2D strip"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:20
#: 428a216bb5bb43b29b7c84d5b9326675
msgid ""
"**3D mesh.** ``gen_cube(chara_length=0.04, ...)`` produces a tetrahedral "
"cube with on the order of 5–10 k DOFs (vs. ~3 k in the 2D strip). Each "
"L-BFGS iteration assembles and integrates over significantly more "
"quadrature points."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:24
#: 2d8075d0d76f4e97ab1f0eed32b3d7a9
#, python-format
msgid ""
"**More load steps.** 50 loading + 50 unloading = 100 steps, reaching 40 %"
" strain — far enough into plasticity that the hardening branch dominates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:27
#: 9a5b589544184697bac0038f4df77264
msgid ""
"**Larger plastic-strain magnitude.** At 40 % nominal strain the small-"
"strain assumption is being stretched (literally); the example is still "
"useful as a regression test of the J2 model but you would not trust the "
"absolute stress numbers far from the elastic regime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:32
#: 576dc895c0174fa993e7f9a6cdc42756
msgid ""
"**Different output.** ``plasticity_3d.mp4`` shows the deformed cube "
"colored by **von Mises stress** plus a force-displacement curve at the "
"loaded face."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:38
#: 2f8da821d5f0439dadbf6a6c12855536
msgid "Code skeleton"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:40
#: d68173b7e2e541e7aa1c7dce313b1123
msgid "examples/solid/plasticity_3d/plasticity_3d.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:67
#: 4824e6246b67428098e05b2f074738be
msgid ""
"The boundary conditions follow the same pattern as the 2D strip: roller "
"on the :math:`x = 0` face, corner pin at the origin, prescribed "
":math:`u_x` on the :math:`x = 0.5` face."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:73
#: ddb792df963a41668638553f183057cd
msgid "Performance notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:75
#: 2ca350a795c8431b8754c222b5d60148
msgid ""
"The 3D problem is L-BFGS-bound — most of the wall-clock time is in the "
"per-iteration energy evaluation + autograd backward. GPU acceleration "
"helps significantly: ``mesh.to(\"cuda\")`` and ``u.to(\"cuda\")`` move "
"the entire optimization to the device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:79
#: e797bb9887ec405689c9ae2d5f382ac9
msgid ""
"History-variable updates (``model.advance_history``) are cheap compared "
"to the per-step L-BFGS sweep; do not worry about optimizing them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_3d.rst:82
#: b6dddb2c9ce04817b41bdbe270147432
msgid ""
"If memory becomes an issue at finer mesh resolutions, set the assembler's"
" ``batch_size`` argument to chunk the per-quadrature-point integrand "
"tensor — see :doc:`../../user_guide/batched_workflows` for the memory "
"story."
msgstr ""

